 Sterkspruit - Sterkspruit police have appealed to the public for assistance in locating two missing people. "Avuyile Civatha a 19-year-old man from Thaba Lesoba Locality was last seen on 8 March 2020," described police spokesperson, Capt Ursula Roelofse. "On the said day he was driving a truck and was involve in an accident where he collided with a quantum at Herschel. "After the incident he was not seen again." She said that in the second case, the 52-year-old Lungephi Matwa from Hinana Locality was last seen on 1 March 2020 when he indicated that he is going to visit his sister at Lepota Locality. "He never arrived at his sister’s house. He is mentally challenged," Capt Roelofse said. "If any person can assist the SAPS in our search for the two men please contact Captain Monica Dinga from the Sterkspruit Detectives at 071 352 51 20." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 